## üìÑ Incident Summary

| Field                 | Details |
|----------------------|---------|
| **Incident Name**     | "CRM Database Exposure - March 2025" |
| **Date Identified**   | 2025-03-14 |
| **Detection Method**  | External security researcher via responsible disclosure |
| **Reported By**       | securityresearcher@example.com |
| **Data Classification** | Confidential |

---

## üîç Affected Assets

| Asset Name / Type      | Description / Location       | Sensitivity Level | Notes                        |
|------------------------|------------------------------|-------------------|------------------------------|
| `crm_clients`          | PostgreSQL DB hosted on AWS  | Confidential      | Contained customer PII       |
| `s3-bucket-crm-export` | AWS S3 Bucket                | Confidential      | Misconfigured to public-read |

---

## üì¶ Leaked Data

| Data Type            | Description / Examples                      | Volume           | Risk Impact |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------|------------------|-------------|
| PII                  | Names, Emails, Phone Numbers                | ~42,000 records  | High        |
| Internal Notes       | Account management notes                    | Moderate volume  | Medium      |

---

## üîê Attack Vector

- **Initial Access Method:** Misconfigured S3 bucket with public-read access enabled.
- **Method of Exfiltration:** Direct access via S3 HTTP endpoint.
- **Persistence (if any):** None found.
- **Indicators of Compromise (IOCs):**
  - S3 Access Logs showed IP: `82.123.45.200`
  - Accessed: `/crm-exports/march2025_customers.csv`
  - User-Agent: `curl/7.68.0`

---

## üßØ Response Actions

| Action                      | Responsible Party | Date       | Status        |
|-----------------------------|-------------------|------------|---------------|
| Block public access to S3   | DevOps            | 2025-03-14 | ‚úÖ Completed   |
| Rotate access keys          | IT Security       | 2025-03-14 | ‚úÖ Completed   |
| Notify affected customers   | Communications    | 2025-03-15 | ‚úÖ Completed   |
| Report to Data Protection Authority | Legal         | 2025-03-15 | ‚úÖ Completed   |
| Enable S3 access logging    | Cloud Admin       | 2025-03-16 | ‚úÖ Completed   |

---

## üîé Root Cause Analysis

- **Summary:** A misconfigured Amazon S3 bucket containing CRM data was left publicly accessible without authentication.
- **Contributing Factors:**
  - No S3 bucket policy enforcement
  - Lack of periodic configuration reviews
  - No automated misconfiguration alerts
- **Detection Gaps:**
  - Cloud posture monitoring tool was not configured
  - DLP solutions were not integrated with cloud storage

---

## üìà Impact Assessment

| Area           | Description |
|----------------|-------------|
| Legal Impact   | GDPR breach; report submitted to the EU DPA |
| Financial      | Estimated $75,000 in incident response, legal fees, and customer support |
| Reputational   | Minimal public attention; minor social media mentions |
| Operational    | 2 days of engineering time to audit all cloud storage |

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Lessons Learned & Recommendations

- Implement **AWS Config Rules** to flag public buckets
- Enforce **S3 bucket policies** that deny public access unless explicitly approved
- Integrate **DLP tools** with cloud environments
- Conduct **quarterly cloud security posture assessments**
- Improve **incident response training** and simulations

---

